SUMMARY:Beginner Mah Jongg Class
DESCRIPTION:Learn how to play American Mah Jongg on Tuesdays at the JCC East Bay with a 4-part class.\nThis 4-part class provides an in-depth\, comprehensive tutorial/course on how to play American Mah Jongg by our esteemed JCC East Bay Mah Jongg instructors. \nBeginner Mah Jongg Class takes place the following four dates and times: \nTuesday\, May 19\, 11am–1pm \nTuesday\, May 26\, 11am–1pm \nTuesday\, June 2\, 11am–1pm \nTuesday\, June 9\, 11am–1pm \nSign up for JCC East Bay Beginner Mah Jongg Class! \nRegister here.
URL:https://jcceastbay.org/events/beginner-mah-jongg-class-4/
LOCATION:JCC East Bay\, 1414 Walnut Street\, Berkeley\, CA\, 94709\, United States
CATEGORIES:Arts & Culture,Older Adults
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://jcceastbay.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/beginner-mah-jongg-mar26.jpg
END:VEVENT
